Totally my fault--I hit "close and comment" but meant to not post my comment at all (or close the PR). I looked through the code and get and post do the same thing so this makes sense to me. The one thing I wasn't sure about was whether you could end up with an empty string key or not and how that'd affect rate limiting. The docs say `request.META['HTTP_X_X']` (and similarly for `.GET` and `.POST`) which is not what the code is doing.

I think this should come with a test. Also the docs should be updated so that they're documenting the behavior more accurately.

@jsocol Does that make sense? Is it possible to end up with an empty string key?

